00:24:30.990 --> 00:24:33.050
Yes, by all means.

00:24:33.050 --> 00:24:35.040
You first, sir.

00:24:35.040 --> 00:24:37.790
&gt;&gt; Questioner: I'm curious.

00:24:37.790 --> 00:24:41.920
Having seen the popular depictions
of things like narcos and whatnot

00:24:41.920 --> 00:24:48.930
in popular culture, are there any
that you're particularly interested

00:24:48.930 --> 00:24:50.890
in and would want to react to?

00:24:50.890 --> 00:24:55.940
Say, for instance, from the
pervasiveness of Escobar

00:24:55.940 --> 00:24:57.820
and thoughts about Columbia?

00:24:57.820 --> 00:25:02.720 position:56%
What are the things you mentioned
earlier that provoke you to respond?

00:25:02.720 --> 00:25:08.380
&gt;&gt; Juan Gabriel Vasquez: I
don't think we have enough time

00:25:08.380 --> 00:25:12.850
to let's talk about one
of those things that are

00:25:12.850 --> 00:25:20.750
in direct relationship with the
other part of your question.

00:25:20.750 --> 00:25:29.750
I have always felt angry
and sad and disappointed

00:25:29.750 --> 00:25:32.090
at this thing we have
called the war on drugs.

00:25:32.090 --> 00:25:34.470
But I think it's a huge mistake.

00:25:34.470 --> 00:25:37.100 position:56%
It has been a huge mistake 30 years.

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:43.100
I think it has damaged and
destroyed people's lives

00:25:43.100 --> 00:25:47.220
in a way that is not justifiable.

00:25:47.220 --> 00:25:51.090
Because drugs are essentially --
this is the situation in my country

00:25:51.090 --> 00:25:57.350 position:56%
and this is the situation in America
too -- drugs are a twofold problem.

00:25:57.350 --> 00:26:03.420
They are a public health issue in
that drug consumption is a problem.

00:26:03.420 --> 00:26:07.350
And they are a public order
issue, in that the fact

00:26:07.350 --> 00:26:15.270
that they are criminalized needs
to criminality, corruption,

00:26:15.270 --> 00:26:18.850
enormous wealth in the wrong hands,

00:26:18.850 --> 00:26:22.530
in the hands of the Mafia,
of criminal structures.

00:26:22.530 --> 00:26:28.890
And that destabilizes
democracies, kills innocent people.

00:26:28.890 --> 00:26:34.620
And I have always defended the
idea that decriminalization

00:26:34.620 --> 00:26:36.800
of drugs would lead us
with only one problem.

00:26:36.800 --> 00:26:41.950
The problem, how to solve the
fact that people take drugs

00:26:41.950 --> 00:26:46.560
and that damages their health.

00:26:46.560 --> 00:26:51.390
The enormous amount of
money we spend on the war

00:26:51.390 --> 00:26:54.680
on drugs could be spent
on prevention,

00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:57.510
treatment, education, etc.

00:26:57.510 --> 00:27:04.000
[ Applause ]

00:27:04.000 --> 00:27:05.380
&gt;&gt; Juan Gabriel Vasquez: Thank you.

00:27:05.380 --> 00:27:06.680
So yeah, that's it.

00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:08.880
As for narcos, I haven't
seen that show.

00:27:08.880 --> 00:27:11.470
