00:27:45.360 --> 00:27:48.060
Was there any corrective
action taken

00:27:48.060 --> 00:27:50.240
against the journalist
by the general?

00:27:50.240 --> 00:27:51.540
That's number one.

00:27:51.540 --> 00:27:55.540
And number two, since you mentioned
that you are a political columnist,

00:27:55.540 --> 00:27:58.330
and I hope I'm getting
my facts right,

00:27:58.330 --> 00:27:59.940
a year ago there was an
agreement [inaudible].

00:27:59.940 --> 00:28:06.160
I just want your commentary
on how does all that progress,

00:28:06.160 --> 00:28:09.610
because we heard there
was an agreement

00:28:09.610 --> 00:28:18.810
and the agreement fell apart and
then something else was going on.

00:28:18.810 --> 00:28:20.110
&gt;&gt; Juan Gabriel Vasquez: Yeah.

00:28:20.110 --> 00:28:26.980
That's kind of a long answer
too, one that I'm glad to give.

00:28:26.980 --> 00:28:31.830
About the peace process, yes, there
was a successful peace process.

00:28:31.830 --> 00:28:36.400
The first successful peace process
in the history of my country,

00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:41.570
a country that has
been at war with itself

00:28:41.570 --> 00:28:45.630
for the best part of
the 20th century.

00:28:45.630 --> 00:28:52.050 position:56%
This kind of violence began in 1948.

00:28:52.050 --> 00:29:00.550
The FARC, the Marxist
guerrilla, was born in 1964.

00:29:00.550 --> 00:29:06.760
The peace negotiations effectively
ended that war, a 52-year-old war

00:29:06.760 --> 00:29:12.040
that had caused almost 7 million
victims, counting the dead,

00:29:12.040 --> 00:29:14.770
the wounded, the displaced
population.

00:29:14.770 --> 00:29:24.300
And that agreement sadly was
defeated in a referendum,

00:29:24.300 --> 00:29:29.300
which to my mind was part of
the same international movement

00:29:29.300 --> 00:29:38.540
of populism fueled with lies,
misrepresentations, and calamities

00:29:38.540 --> 00:29:43.970
that caused Brexit and
a certain president.

00:29:45.910 --> 00:29:51.640
[Laughter] That was a sad
day for Colombians who think

00:29:51.640 --> 00:29:59.630
that the peace process, the
negotiation, was the way to go.

00:29:59.630 --> 00:30:09.940
But after that, the agreements
were passed by Congress.

00:30:10.960 --> 00:30:14.750
So they are being implemented
right now.

00:30:14.750 --> 00:30:21.240
The parties modified the agreements
in almost every way that was asked

00:30:21.240 --> 00:30:27.040
by the opposition, and they
are now being implemented.

00:30:27.040 --> 00:30:36.000
There was a picture of the
paper six or seven months ago

00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:42.530
in which the biggest room in
the military hospital in Bogotá,

00:30:42.530 --> 00:30:49.150
a room that used to be
filled with wounded soldiers,

00:30:49.150 --> 00:30:52.970
was empty for the first
time in 50 years.

00:30:52.970 --> 00:30:59.880
[Applause] That was a good moment.

00:30:59.880 --> 00:31:05.930
That's the situation.

00:31:05.930 --> 00:31:08.700
And your other question was?

00:31:08.700 --> 00:31:10.000
&gt;&gt; Questioner: The libel laws.

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:11.300
&gt;&gt; Juan Gabriel Vasquez: Yeah.

00:31:11.300 --> 00:31:18.660
Freedom of expression is
protected in very effective ways

00:31:18.660 --> 00:31:23.970
in my country from what I can see.

00:31:23.970 --> 00:31:33.580
That doesn't prevent the most
radical politicians to circumvent

00:31:33.580 --> 00:31:37.390
